TY  - JOUR
AU  - Akerlof, George A.
T1  - Labor Contracts as Partial Gift Exchange*
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885099
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 97
IS  - 4
SP  - 543
EP  - 569
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper explains involuntary unemployment in terms of the response of firms to workers' group behavior. Workers' effort depends upon the norms determining a fair day's work. In order to affect those norms, firms may pay more than the market-clearing wage. Industries that pay consistently more than the market-clearing wage are primary, and those that pay only the market-clearing wage are secondary. Thus, this paper also gives a theory for division of labor markets between primary and secondary.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885099
ER  - 



